                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-235-off1254 t18280410-235-victim1317"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>WILLIAM STOKER. I <rs id="t18280410-235-viclabel1256" type="occupation">kept a pork-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-235-victim1317 t18280410-235-viclabel1256"></join> in <placeName id="t18280410-235-crimeloc1257">Bethnal Green</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-235-crimeloc1257" type="placeName" value="Bethnal Green"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-235-crimeloc1257" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-235-off1254 t18280410-235-crimeloc1257"></join>. On the 22d of March, I was crossing to my own house, and saw the prisoner come out of my shop; she looked in at the window, then turned the corner, into another street - I went in and asked my wife if she had sold anything, she said, No; I went out and saw the prisoner with another woman - they separated on seeing me, and went up to the prisoner who had a basket; I asked what she had there; she said, "That woman gave it to me; she opened the basket, and there was a hand of pork in it - I said, "Have you not got a leg?" she said, she knew nothing of that - I took her back to the shop; I went for an officer, and when I returned, she had dropped a leg of pork from under her clothes; I am sure she is the woman who came out of the shop.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did you see her within the shop? A. I saw her just on the top step of the door; I did not say she was holding up her gown with her other hand - she had a great cloak on.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-235-person1318">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18280410-235-person1318" type="surname" value="HAWKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-235-person1318" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-235-person1318" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a butcher. On the 22d of March, I was standing two doors from the prosecutor's shop and saw a crowd there; I went up and saw the leg of pork drop from under the prisoner's cloak - I took it up.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Had she been searched before? A. No; she was near the counter - I am certain it did not fall from the counter; the basket was on the counter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-235-person1319">
                  HENRY 
                  RICE
               <interp inst="t18280410-235-person1319" type="surname" value="RICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-235-person1319" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-235-person1319" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I saw a mob and went into this house, and took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 21.</p>
